{
  "page": "Defender of the Citadel",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Defender of the Citadel</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> also called <b>Protector of the Citadel</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> is one of the hereditary titles held by the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hightower\" title=\"House Hightower\">House Hightower</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a>, the center of the order of <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\">maesters</a>, was established on a tract of land granted by King <a href=\"/index.php/Urrigon_Hightower\" title=\"Urrigon Hightower\">Urrigon Hightower</a> and ever since, House Hightower has been a patron of the order.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_oldtown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_oldtown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Leyton_Hightower\" title=\"Leyton Hightower\">Leyton Hightower</a> is the current possessor of the title.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Defender_of_the_Citadel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"